{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:galatians.1",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "galatians",
    "chapterNumber": 1,
    "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1",
    "summary": "Source text for Galatians 1 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.1.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:1",
      "text": "Paul, an apostle— not from men, nor through man, but through Jesus Christ, and God the Father, who raised him from the dead —",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.1.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:2",
      "text": "and all the brothers who are with me, to the assemblies of Galatia:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.1.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:3",
      "text": "Grace to you and peace from God the Father and our Lord Jesus Christ,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.1.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:4",
      "text": "who gave himself for our sins, that he might deliver us out of this present evil age, according to the will of our God and Father —",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.1.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:5",
      "text": "to whom be the glory forever and ever. Amen.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.1.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:6",
      "text": "I marvel that you are so quickly deserting him who called you in the grace of Christ to a different “good news”,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.1.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:7",
      "text": "but there isn’t another “good news.” Only there are some who trouble you and want to pervert the Good News of Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.1.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:8",
      "text": "But even though we, or an angel from heaven, should preach to you any “good news” other than that which we preached to you, let him be cursed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.1.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:9",
      "text": "As we have said before, so I now say again: if any man preaches to you any “good news” other than that which you received, let him be cursed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.1.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:10",
      "text": "For am I now seeking the favor of men, or of God? Or am I striving to please men? For if I were still pleasing men, I wouldn’t be a servant of Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.1.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:11",
      "text": "But I make known to you, brothers, concerning the Good News which was preached by me, that it is not according to man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.1.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:12",
      "text": "For I didn’t receive it from man, nor was I taught it, but it came to me through revelation of Jesus Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.1.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:13",
      "text": "For you have heard of my way of living in time past in the Jews’ religion, how that beyond measure I persecuted the assembly of God and ravaged it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.1.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:14",
      "text": "I advanced in the Jews’ religion beyond many of my own age among my countrymen, being more exceedingly zealous for the traditions of my fathers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.1.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:15",
      "text": "But when it was the good pleasure of God, who separated me from my mother’s womb and called me through his grace,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.1.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:16",
      "text": "to reveal his Son in me, that I might preach him among the Gentiles, I didn’t immediately confer with flesh and blood,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.1.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:17",
      "text": "nor did I go up to Jerusalem to those who were apostles before me, but I went away into Arabia. Then I returned to Damascus.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.1.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:18",
      "text": "Then after three years I went up to Jerusalem to visit Peter, and stayed with him fifteen days.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.1.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:19",
      "text": "But of the other apostles I saw no one except James, the Lord’s brother.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.1.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:20",
      "text": "Now about the things which I write to you, behold, before God, I’m not lying.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.1.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:21",
      "text": "Then I came to the regions of Syria and Cilicia.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.1.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:22",
      "text": "I was still unknown by face to the assemblies of Judea which were in Christ,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.1.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:23",
      "text": "but they only heard, “He who once persecuted us now preaches the faith that he once tried to destroy.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.1.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:24",
      "text": "So they glorified God in me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
